# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
# .claude/: ignore per-user state, track shared skills + project settings
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json

# Per-user .claude/ in nested folders (e.g., incorporation templates)
docs/incorporation/templates/.claude/
supabase/.temp/
*.timestamp-*

# Testing artifacts
coverage/
playwright-report/
test-results/
nul

# Python bytecode (used by docs/exports/ scripts)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Confidential incorporation artifacts — filled term sheets and signed
# documents must NEVER be committed to the public repo. See
# docs/incorporation/templates/signing-logistics-guide.md for the policy.
# (Templates without dates remain tracked.)
docs/incorporation/founder-term-sheet-*.md
docs/incorporation/founder-term-sheet-*.pdf
docs/incorporation/signed/

# Office app temp/lock files
~$*

# Confidential financial model — the .gs source (in docs/financials/) is safe
# to commit because it contains only structure + formulas. The generated
# .xlsx artifacts contain real revenue projections, funding ask numbers,
# and founder context, and MUST NEVER be committed. The artifact lives in
# the user's OneDrive and is shared with co-founders directly.
docs/financials/*.xlsx
docs/financials/*.xls
docs/financials/*.csv

# Confidential strategy & legal source documents — the rent-a-vacation/rav-website
# repo is PUBLIC. Files matched here must never be committed (or re-committed if
# they are already tracked). Note: patterns below preventively block future
# additions; legal dossier + compliance brief PDFs that are already tracked
# require a separate git-history scrub to fully remove (deferred — see
# project_legal_dossier_scrub_pending.md memory).
docs/legal/Legal_Dossier_*.pdf
docs/legal/RAV_Compliance_Brief_*.pdf
docs/features/rami/
docs/competitive-intelligence/
**/competitor-analysis/
RAMI-Agent-Build-Prompt-*.docx
RAV-Competitive-Intelligence-*.docx
